    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_ReportTotalsByMonthAndAgency",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to generate a report of total dollar amounts by month and agency for a given scenario. It dynamically constructs and executes a SQL query to pivot data from a view ("
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "budget.vwTotalBudget",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ") based on the fiscal year associated with the provided scenario ID. The result is a dataset where each row represents an agency, and each column represents a billing period within the fiscal year, showing the total dollars for that period."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves dynamic SQL construction, pivoting data, and handling input parameters, which adds a moderate level of complexity. The use of dynamic SQL requires careful handling to ensure security and performance, and the pivot operation requires a good understanding of SQL transformations."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
